Semantic Router Intent Classification Flow. User Query -> Intent Classifier (GPT-4o-mini) -> Four Routes: SIMPLE (GPT-4o-mini, 256 tokens), COMPLEX (Claude Sonnet 4, 2048 tokens), CODE (Codestral, 1024 tokens), REFUSAL (Blocked). Each route checks Semantic Cache first. Cache Hit: Return cached. Cache Miss: Call Model -> Store in Cache. Router Optimization: Embedding-based kNN (10ms), Fine-tuned MiniLM, Regex Rules for Simple Intents. Cost per route annotated. German labels.